INSERT INTO `sk_article` VALUES ('40', '35', 'Laboratory introduce', '', '#000000', '1', '&lt;p&gt;\n	State Key Laboratory (hereinafter referred to as the laboratory) in 1985 approved by the state construction, in 1989 passed the acceptance and officially opened. Research center mainly includes chemistry room, preparation room, pharmacology, molecular biology room, the chromatographic chamber, cell culture animal room and a temporary raising chamber and so on, which first four laboratory is located in the life science and Technology Museum upstairs, cell culture room located in the laboratory building 310 room, animal temporary raising chamber located in the ground floor, the southwest side. Welcome to the school teachers and students to make an appointment, we will serve you wholeheartedly.\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;img src=&quot;/pro/public_html/Uploads/image/20150905/55ea774171e29.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:left;&quot;&gt;\n	In the 407 room, chemical synthesis, natural medicine and other aspects of the study, such as the chemical reaction to generate new compounds, isolated from natural resources to purify a single set of classification. The upstream samples prepared by chemical laboratory can be used for the study of the use of the pharmacology, preparation room and molecular laboratory. In order to improve the usability and the advanced nature of the laboratory, the main apparatus including the high pressure reaction kettle, the automatic fraction collector and the homogenate machine. Located in the 409 room, can be processed products, including cosmetics, health care products and drugs, etc.. The main equipment includes nano - homogeneous, high - pressure homogenization and paste filling machine. The laboratory space is limited, and the preparation room also has some other functions. Located in the 411 room, the main drugs for animal behavior / disease status of the study. The laboratory by Dr. Feng Binbin and Professor Zhang Jianhai\'s planning, and has been put into use for many years, so the laboratory conditions are relatively mature. Department of pharmacology major equipment including animal treadmill test, brain stereotaxic instrument, water maze video analysis system, open field test video analysis system and darkroom experiment video analysis system. Located in the 413 room, the laboratory can carry out molecular experiments, such as DNA, RNA and protein extraction and electrophoresis experiments, the preparation of competent cells, molecular cloning, electrophoretic patterns, can be carried out by microbial shock. To buy PCR meter, gel imaging analyzer and microwave ovens, etc.. Located in room 406, mainly for sample separation and analysis. The laboratory of the liquid chromatograph for Agilent products, equipped with manual sample and automatic sampling device, detector includes a UV detector, fluorescence detector and evaporative light scattering detector; gas chromatograph is Agilent products, equipped with headspace sampling device. Gas chromatography and liquid chromatography can be used for the identification and determination of most drugs. Located in the experimental building 310 room, the laboratory can carry out the research of cells, such as cell recovery, subculture, frozen storage. Also equipped with ultra low temperature refrigerator, the sample can be ultra low temperature preservation. Fluorescence inverted microscope can observe the special morphology of cells after staining. Laboratories focus on academic cooperation and exchanges, and domestic and foreign famous universities and scientific research institutions established extensive contacts, five years, held international and domestic academic conferences 12 times, invite domestic and foreign well-known scholars and experts to laboratory academic report 126, selected academic backbone of academic exchanges at home and abroad 120 people, in important domestic and international academic conference do special report 14 games. Laboratory research condition is good. With more than 5000 square meters of office building and value 3591 million yuan of instruments and equipment, which 30 million yuan of above equipment 16, including high performance computing system, grid computing systems, software testing system, 3D simulation system, cloud computing platform, analysis and design modeling software platform. To implement the policy of &quot;open, mobile, United, and competition&quot; in the laboratory, the basic research of software engineering and application, and the key technology of software engineering, and the construction of laboratory into the field of software engineering.\n&lt;/p&gt;', './Uploads/image/20150905/55ea7726b2b46.jpg', '0', '0', null, '1', '本站', 'admin11', '1', '0', '1441429373', '2', '1441429373', '0', '', '2');
INSERT INTO `sk_article` VALUES ('41', '36', 'Research direction', '', '#337FE5', '1', 'Genomic instability and 9-1-1 protein complex:&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n	In the process of cell division, DNA contains the genetic information of living organisms, and the DNA is copied and transmitted to the next generation, the high fidelity of DNA replication, and the stability of the organism. However, in living cells, the cells are subjected to damage (Figure 1) at all times. If the damage is not repaired, the normal life activity of the cells will be destroyed, and the life of the cells will be destroyed, which will lead to a series of genetic diseases. The occurrence of cancer is usually caused by mutations in the gene. In most cases, the genomic instability (instability genomic) in human life will eventually lead to the accumulation of sufficient mutations and eventually produce cancer (Figure two). Many of the DNA damage is spontaneously generated, and even in some cases the frequency is high, so, in the absence of DNA damage agent in the environment, DNA repair system defects will cause a lot of problems. DNA damage factors include two aspects of cellular endogenous and environmental factors. Endogenous factors include DNA replication errors, cell metabolic activity of chemicals (such as free radicals, alkylating agent) attack. The exogenous factors include ultraviolet radiation, radiation, pollutant, cigarette burning, and virus.\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:left;&quot;&gt;\n	&lt;img src=&quot;/pro/public_html/Uploads/image/20150905/55ea791c475da.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:left;&quot;&gt;\n	In normal cells, there is a complete system of DNA damage repair and cell cycle monitoring, maintenance of genome stability. The DNA repair and cell cycle checkpoint mechanism in malignant tumor cells is defective, and the genome is highly variable. The gene mutation of the gene in the genome, which has the characteristics of high frequency mutation, changes the characteristics of the cells, and eventually causes the cells to control the growth and metastasis. The cells in the picture are divided from a colon cancer cell. The red dot is the third chromosome and the yellow dot is the twelfth chromosome. Normal cell chromosomes pair, and the pair are also paired with a pair of chromosomes. But some cells in the picture have only one red dot, a little bit of only a yellow dot, which indicates that the C et al. Nature (Lengauer, 1998) has been lost. Another problem with defects in DNA repair system is we wouldn\'t from parent there was inherited and thus the perpetuation of the species and existence will be problems. However, the replication of DNA cannot be absolutely precise, otherwise it will not make the species evolve to adapt to the changing environment. Multiple DNA repair system in the cell is the monitoring system of these two tasks. An interesting phenomenon is that all of the biological macromolecules, only DNA in the damaged will be repaired, the other large molecules in the damaged are only to be replaced by new molecules, which is also confirmed by the other side of the DNA in the vital status of the organism. Cause DNA damage factors, according to different sources is divided into two categories, first class for endogenous injury factor, including the following: DNA replication errors; spontaneous lesions including base tautomerism, base de ammonia (C, u, a, I) and base loss; oxidative metabolic by-products such as reactive oxygen species of reactive oxygen species (ROS) attack. The second damage factors in the environment, including radiation (ultraviolet and X-ray); chemical carcinogenesis (oxidation deamination, alkylating agents or metabolic activator such as benzopyrene, Aspergillus flavus elements produce base complexes). In the long evolutionary process, a set of precision and effective defense system to deal with the damage, according to statistics, there are more than one hundred kinds of proteins involved in the damage repair DNA. The system is like a group of organizations that are organized in an orderly manner to work in order to protect the stability of the genome of the organism. These responses to DNA damage include: (1) the removal of DNA damage and restore the DNA double chain continuity (2) activated cell cycle monitoring points, so that the cell cycle progression to efficient repair of damaged DNA (3) to maintain genomic stability, prevent the occurrence of disease. DNA damage repair and cell cycle monitoring are two key mechanisms to maintain genome stability. The DNA damage repair and cell cycle control of malignant tumor cells are defective, and the genome is highly unstable. The 9-1-1 protein complex is composed of Rad9, Hus1, and Rad1 (Fig. three). 9-1-1 complex can be set in the DNA double chain sliding. Rad9, Hus1 and Rad1 are highly conserved in biological evolution. Human Rad9 gene can partially replace the function of Rad9 gene in fission yeast. 9-1-1 complex plays a key role in DNA damage repair and cell cycle monitoring, which is an important factor to maintain genome stability. Our study showed that in mice, the mice were susceptible to tumor (Figure four), except for Rad9 or Rad1. DNA damage includes base level, nucleotide level, single strand breaks, double strand breaks, chain and inter strand cross-linking. Biological evolution is different from the repair approach to repair various types of DNA damage. We and several other laboratory studies have indicated that the 9-1-1 complex is involved in the repair of many kinds of DNA damage.\n&lt;/p&gt;', '', '0', '0', null, '1', '本站', 'admin11', '1', '0', '1441429824', '2', '1441429824', '0', '', '2');
